    "It seems natural to interpret objections based in the 'coupling-constitution fallacy' as blocking IC by targeting P1.",
    "We can reformulate this as suggesting that acts of offloading are just not the kinds of things that could constitute human cognition, though (as per the evidence canvassed in §3.1) they are intimately bound up with it.",
